This is slightly hard to test, one either has to modify the code to add an attribute, create a stack, then remove the code that removes the attribute, or do db surgery to add an attribute.  The latter is simpler.  One way to do so is to create a stack that contains a security group, find the appropriate record in the eucalyptus_cloudformation.stack_resources table and do something like this:

{code}
update stack_resources set resource_attributes_json = '{"GroupId":"\"sg-6c30a4b7\"","PhantomAttribute":\"PhantomValue\"}' where resource_attributes_json = '{"GroupId":"\"sg-6c30a4b7\""}';
{code}

This will add a phantom attribute in the group, which should trigger the case here.
